After payment:
Coins are credited to wallet
User can start interaction
Interaction After Recharge
Once wallet is recharged, user can:
Chat with creator
Send messages
Subscribe to creator
Join Live Stream
Book Video Call
Book Audio Call
All actions depend on:
Creator’s fee structure
Available wallet balance
Important Business Logic
Users must recharge before paid interaction
Creator fees may differ for followers & subscribers
Android and iOS packs are different
Coins are required for all paid services

How User Uses Chat Feature
Starting Chat
User follows a creator
Once followed → Chat room becomes active
Chat room is visible on
User side
Creator side
 Chat Messaging Logic
User sends messages to creator
Charges are applied per message based on creator’s fee setup
Coins are deducted automatically from user’s wallet


 Pay-Per-View (PPV) Content
Creator can send:
Images
Videos
Documents
These can be:
Free
Paid (PPV – Pay Per View)
If content is paid:
User sees locked content
User clicks to unlock
Coins are deducted
User can view that specific PPV file

How User Uses Live Stream Feature
Live Notification
If a followed creator goes live:
User receives notification
Live status appears on:


Home Page
Chat section (showing “Creator is Live”)


Joining Live Stream
User clicks on live notification
Enters live stream
Access and pricing depend on:
User role (Follower / Subscriber)
Creator’s live stream fee setup
User pays coins based on:
Follower price OR
Subscriber price


Live Stream Goals
During live stream:
Users can support creator
Help creator complete live goals
Interact in real time

How User Uses Tip Feature
If the user has sufficient wallet balance, they can tip creators.
Tips can be sent via:
 Post Tip
 Chat Tip
 Call Tip
 Live Stream Tip
Process:
User selects tip option
Enters tip amount
Coins are deducted
Creator receives tip
From chat screen:
User selects Audio or Video Call
User chooses call duration (example: 30 minutes)
Sends call request


Coin Hold Logic
When call request is sent:
Required coins are put on hold
Coins are temporarily deducted but not finalized
 If Creator Accepts
Creator accepts request
Creator schedules call
At scheduled time → Call starts
After call completion → Coins are finalized
Refund Conditions
Coins are refunded if:
Creator does not accept request
Call is not completed
Call fails in 3 attempts
In such cases:
Held coins are returned to user wallet



 How Home Page Post Visibility & User Interaction Flow
The Home Page displays creator posts based on the user’s relationship (Follower or Subscriber) with the creator.
 Post Visibility Based on User Role
Post visibility depends on whether the user is a:
Follower
Subscriber
 If User is a Follower
User can:
View follower-only posts
Like the post
Comment on the post
Send Tip
Share the post
Follower cannot view subscriber-only posts.
If User is a Subscriber
User can:
View follower posts
View subscriber-only posts
Like posts
Comment on posts
Send Tip
Share posts
Subscribers get access to both follower and subscriber content.
 Available Actions on Posts
On each visible post, user can:
 Like
 Comment
 Tip (Send coins to creator)
 Share
All interactions depend on the user’s role.

how user use user side setting options?
Users can access Settings from their profile or menu section.
The Settings section allows users to manage their account, wallet, subscriptions, and app-related information.
Edit Profile
Using Edit Profile, users can update their personal information:
Add / Update Cover Image
Add / Update Profile Image
Add Full Name
Set Username
Add Bio
After updating → Save changes → Profile updates successfully.
 Subscribed
The Subscribed section shows:
List of creators the user has subscribed to
Subscription status:
Active
Inactive
This helps users track their active and expired subscriptions.
Following
The Following section shows:
List of creators the user is following
Users can view and manage the creators they follow.
Change Password
Using Change Password, users can:
Enter current password
Enter new password
Confirm new password
Save changes
Password gets updated successfully.
Get Verified
If a regular user wants to become a creator:
Click Get Verified
Apply for creator verification
Submit required details
Wait for admin approval
After approval → User account becomes Creator account.
Transaction History
The Transaction section allows users to:
View coin spending history
See where coins were used:
Chat
Live Stream
Calls
Tips
Subscriptions
It provides full transparency of wallet usage.
Wallet
Using Wallet, users can:
Recharge their e-wallet
Check available coin balance
View recharge history
Blocked Accounts
If a user blocks any creator:
Blocked creator appears in Blocked Accounts list
User can:
View blocked creators
Unblock them anytime
Account Management
Using Account Management, users can:
Delete their FAHDU account permanently
Once deleted:
Account access is removed
Terms & Policies
Users can view:
Terms & Conditions
 Privacy Policy
 Refund Policy
These pages explain FAHDU’s rules and policies.
About
The About section shows:
FAHDU app version
Basic app information
Help Center
Using Help Center, users can:
Contact FAHDU Admin
Report issues
Raise complaints
Ask questions regarding payments, calls, subscriptions, etc.
 Logout
Using Logout, users can:
Log out of their FAHDU account
Return to login screen
